The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 New Detroit centre 

 Chennai, Feb. 3 (PTI): Satyam Computer Services has unveiled its state-of-the-art Automotive Centre of Excellence in Detroit to enable better customer interaction.

 Satyam is planning to follow it up with similar facilities at Chennai, Tokyo and a city in Germany, Subu D. Subramanian, director and senior vice-president of the companys manufacturing and automotive business unit, told reporters via video conference from Detroit. The centre, built over 6,000 sq ft, would house over 50 engineers initially. The centre will focus on industry-specific solutions and research and development.

 The initial investment for all the four centres put together would be about $12 million and would require about $5 million to $7 million year-on-year, he said. 




